4.00	Punokawan	Punokawan	In Javanese wayang (shadow puppets), the punokawan are the clown servants of the hero. There are four of them â€“ Semar (also known as Ki Lurah Semar), Petruk, Gareng and Bagong. Semar is the personification of a deity, sometimes said to the be the dhanyang or guardian spirit of the island of Java. In Javanese mythology, deities can only manifest themselves as ugly or otherwise unprepossessing humans, and so Semar is always portrayed as short and fat with a pug nose and a dangling hernia.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/93/COLLECTIE_TROPENMUSEUM_Wajang_wong_voorstelling_%27Jaya_Semadi_en_Sri_Suwela%27_in_de_kraton_van_de_sultan_van_Jogjakarta_TMnr_60002058.jpg/220px-COLLECTIE_TROPENMUSEUM_Wajang_wong_voorstelling_%27Jaya_Semadi_en_Sri_Suwela%27_in_de_kraton_van_de_sultan_van_Jogjakarta_TMnr_60002058.jpg
